The Hydraulic Co said itsBridgeport Hydraulic Co subsidiary had its proposal to use landsales proceeds to help fund capital improvements denied by theConnecticut Department of Public Utility Control.    Hydraulic said its proposal also called for a distributionof the finaical benefits to its stockholders and customers.    However, Hyraulic said the state utility commission wouldconsider similar requests in the future. It said the utilitycommission felt its request was premature and noted  Hydraulicdid not specify parcels of land considered for sale.    The company said it will submit a detailed plan shortly. Reuter&#3;